    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Baron
                            <persName type="to">Saurma</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of yesterday in relation to the provisions of Schedule E,
                    182½, of the new tariff act, touching the levying in certain cases of an
                    additional duty of one-tenth of a cent per pound on sugar from countries that
                    pay a bounty thereon.</p>
                <p>As soon as I have opportunity to give due consideration to the important question
                    and take the President’s direction thereon, I will do myself the honor to reply
                    to your note.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
